                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is pretty clear there is no love in SOE for enchanters.  It is unlikely we will see much in the way of survivability in the short term.
<br />

<br />
So, it looks like Mr. Doppleganger is it.  What I would like to start is a discussion of Doppleganger.  Are there tricks you use to make the chance of it working?  What happened when it didn't work?  From this, we can help each other in two ways.  The first is if there is something you can do that will help it to actually work The other is if we can identify specific problem areas and possibly get SOE to address those.
<br />

<br />
Right now, I'm observed it working somewhat less than 50% of the time.  I don't use it a tremendous amount, so there isn't much data, but here are some general observations:
<br />

<br />
1)  Mr D generates hate.  Early on, I popped him on a Shadowhaven Guard (nonKoS to me).  They destroyed him, then ran after me.  I'll have to test it again, as I'm not sure it was the popping that generated the hate or Mr D's substantial (cough) melee skills that did it.
<br />

<br />
2)  The shadowstep puts you closer to the mob a lot of the time.  After all, the mob is in your face now, so a shadowstep forward will put you closer to him, although on the other side.
<br />

<br />
3)  Shadowstepping to the side can be a problem.  I used to stand off to the side of the raid to I can see better.  That doesn't work well if you are near water or lava and shadowstep that way.
<br />

<br />
4)  One suggestion is to stay in the crowd more, then when you pop Mr D, there will be others nearby.  I can't say if that really works.  I am often shadowstepped closer to the mob (particularly ones with a long reach), and low health agro can be a problem.
<br />

<br />
5)  The reuse timer is still too long.  Maybe if it always worked it would be OK, but I'm getting it to fail so often that the effective working use of it is over an hour.  Even at 15 minutes, I would still view it as a last-ditch escape.
<br />

<br />

<br />
So, let's have your suggestions and observations about how to improve its chance of working.  Also, let us know when it doesn't work and maybe we can get Brenlo to take the concerns seriously enough to talk to a developer with actual data.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
