                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Upgrades to Mr D don't do anything on any kind of challenging content.  I would recommend that Mr D be changed to spawn multiple dopplegangers at higher levels: more HPs is optional (would help them survive AoEs) but unnessicary.
<br />

<br />
The shadowstep is both dangerous (it can send you too far) and inconsistent (it can send you within the melee range of the mob).
<br />

<br />
After Mr D, you are often if not always the #2 (behind Mr D) thing on the mobs hate list.  Which means that you get attacked if you are within melee range.  While I can see the problems with a full-on-fade from Mr D, some kind of partial-hate-wipe (be it a boggle effect of some kind, or fade mixed with an increase hate(1), or a rogue-like evade (not fade, evade)) might be justified.  Then Mr D will have lots of hate, while the enchanter will be near the bottom of the hate list, which means that even if we are in melee range we aren't the preferred target to another PC.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
