<br />
I thought they gave their owner a small fraction of the hate they generate?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Mobs seem to attack someone else pretty much any time someone else is closer than you are after dopple in my experience.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You have to be out of melee range, they have to be on the mob's hate list and in melee range.
<br />

<br />
If both of these things are true, the mob will turn off you and attack the other person.
<br />

<br />
Note that anything you do to increase your own hate at this point will get you summoned and eaten.  It isn't a free lunch, it is a one-off escape.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
