                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Correct or not, it is my belief that you "have aggro" if you appear anywhere on the Hate List, <span style="font-style: italic">including at 0 or even negative numbers.</span> This is why you can pull with successful boggles.
<br />

<br />
Mem Blurs/fades/FD don't decrease aggro, they either remove the player from the Hate List entirely or wipe the Hate List clear.
<br />

<br />
It seems highly probably to me that being the owner of a charmed pet gets you added to the Hate List of any mob it attacks but does not actually give you hate (i.e. you appear on the list but with 0 actual hate). 
<br />

<br />
I've never ever believed the idea that we are building cumulative hate based off the DPS/damage our pets put out. I've just never seen that kind of anger toward me when an ex-pet dies.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ariu <span style="font-style: italic">stop destroying my class damnit!</span> Vil''''Aki &lt;Heroes&gt;</a>
